PART 6: IS INTERVAL THE GLOBAL MAX FOR ALL n ≥ 19?
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  n=3: H(interval) =        3, P(n) =        3  = MAX
  n=4: H(interval) =        4, P(n) =        5  < MAX (5)
  n=5: H(interval) =       15, P(n) =       15  = MAX
  n=6: H(interval) =       18, P(n) =       45  < MAX (45)
  n=7: H(interval) =      175, P(n) =      189  < MAX (189)
  n=8: H(interval) =      312, P(n) =      661  < MAX (661)
  n=9: H(interval) =     3267, P(n) =     3357  < MAX (3357)
  n=10: H(interval) =     6860, P(n) =    15745  < MAX (15745)
  n=11: H(interval) =    93027, P(n) =    95095  < MAX (95095)

===========================================================================
PART 7: ALON'S OPEN CONJECTURE: C(T_n) = C(n)?
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Alon conjectures the interval tournament maximizes Hamiltonian CYCLES.
  'It seems plausible that C(T_n) = C(n), but at the moment we are
  unable to prove or disprove this statement.' (1990)

  Our OCF analysis suggests this IS true for large n:
  The interval's local structure creates better vertex-disjoint
  cycle packings, and the OCF's 2^k weighting amplifies this.
  The crossover at p=19 for paths likely also holds for cycles.

DONE.
